id: pm-b3e9
title: Pre-install package-owned command names should hint the owning package install command
description: "2026-07-04 sandbox review: in a fresh workspace, pm completion/guide/templates fail with generic unknown-command guidance (examples: pm --help, pm activity --help). These names are known package-owned surfaces (pm-guide-shell, pm-templates); unknown-command guidance should map known first-party package command roots to a hint like: install with pm install guide-shell --project. Keeps never-block promise for the pre-install experience."
type: Task
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,audit-followup,extensions
created_at: "2026-07-04T06:30:00.437Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T14:17:56.410Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "Every package-owned command root (completion*, shell, guide, templates, calendar/cal, comments-audit, dedupe-audit, dedupe-merge, normalize, reindex, search-advanced, test-runs) yields an install hint naming the owning package pre-install."
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: medium
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T06:44:03.343Z",maintainer-agent,"Fixed same session: KNOWN_PACKAGE_COMMAND_HINTS extended from 4 entries (guide/templates/calendar/cal) to all package-owned command roots — completion + completion-statuses/tags/types + shell (guide-shell), comments-audit/dedupe-audit/dedupe-merge/normalize (governance-audit), reindex/search-advanced (search-advanced), test-runs (linked-test-adapters). Aliases verified against packages/*/package.json pm.aliases."
  "2026-07-04T07:09:09.322Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-04 verified live in fresh workspace: guide/shell/completion/templates/calendar/reindex/test-runs/dedupe-audit/normalize all yield owning-package install hints pre-install. Also deduped the doubled install step (commander-usage generic hint vs specific hint) in buildKnownPackageCommandGuidance."
body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 sandbox review: in a fresh workspace, `pm completion`, `pm guide`, `pm templates` fail with generic unknown-command guidance (suggesting pm --help / pm activity --help) even though these are known first-party package-owned command roots (pm-guide-shell, pm-templates). Pre-install UX breaks the never-block promise.\n\n## Approach\nMaintain a static map of first-party package-owned command roots → owning package alias (derivable from the bundled catalog, same source as pm-jqd2's alias matching). When unknown-command dispatch misses, check the map first and emit: \"command 'guide' is provided by the guide-shell package — install with: pm install guide-shell --project\".\n\n## Definition of done\nFresh workspace: every bundled package-owned root command name yields the owning install hint; unknown non-package names keep the current did-you-mean; hint catalog covered by spec (install-hint catalog was 4→16 in the 2026-07-04 review — reuse it)."
